  "texts": [
    "The post hoc test results revealed that the EXPOSITIVE bot promoted active searches compared to the PLAIN bot.",
    "The above findings suggest that if the answer of the SUGGESTIVE bot ended with a suggestion regarding the existence of positive/negative opinions, participants were willing to ask questions to the bot more than what they would do with the PLAIN and EXPOSITIVE bots, which proactively and explicitly describe positive/negative opinions.",
    "This tendency could be stronger if the SUGGESTIVE ++ bot displayed links to issue queries for viewing detailed information on positive/negative opinions.",
    "The length of the participant reports submitted as task answers was considered as a metric to examine the decision-making level promoted by the four chatbot types.",
    "Figure 5C illustrates the mean and standard error of the token-based opinion length."
